can i use dhcp to connect on campus and at stanford west stanford answers stanford university stanford answers can i use dhcp to connect on campus and at stanford west categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home can i use dhcp to connect on campus and at stanford west search this site yes submit a helpsu request or call 5 help and select option 2 we will need the hardware address of your computer to complete the request please see determining your hardware address for help on finding the hardware address if you need to connect from both stanford west and on the campus network specify that when you order network services in stanford west and the roaming option will be enabled for your stanford west registration this will allow you to connect to any campus network with a pool of roaming addresses available when using dhcp at stanford remember the following it's best to connect to your machine by its ip address if you need to connect to your machine by its hostname because you are running a web or ssh server be aware that the name of your machine doesn t follow you between locations each hardware address must be registered for dhcp to work properly stanford west & welch road internet stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
